[5] Malta: 1st report
Date: Sat 28 May 2022
Source: Times of Malta [abridged, edited]
https://timesofmalta.com/articles/view/malta-detects-first-monkeypox-case.958072


Malta has detected its 1st case of monkeypox, the Health Ministry said in a statement on Saturday [28 May 2022].

The case involves a 38-year-old man who lives in Malta and who recently travelled to a country where cases of the infection had been detected.

The man has slight symptoms and is isolated at home after it was concluded he did not require hospital treatment.

