[6] Argentina: 2nd case, ex Spain
Date: Sun 29 May 2022
Source: Corrientes [in Spanish, trans. Mod.TY, edited]
http://corrientesenelaire.com.ar/noticia/13972_viruela-del-mono-confirmaron-el-segundo-caso-en-la-argentina.htm


The National Ministry of Public Health reported that "the result of the PCR amplification reaction of the sample taken from the 2nd high-probability case is positive. This confirms infection with poxviruses belonging to the West-African group of the _Orthopoxvirus_ genus. This result is consistent with the observation made by negative staining by transmission electron microscopy, where viral particles of the said viral genus were detected," the Ministry of Health reported in a statement.

Thus, the 2nd case of monkeypox in the country was confirmed. The unit led by Carla Vizzotti said that "it corresponds to a resident in Spain, who is visiting the Province of Buenos Aires and who has no connection with the 1st case."

According to official information, "the person has ulcerative lesions without other associated symptoms, arrived in the country on 25 May [2022] and symptoms began yesterday, 26 May 2022."

Regarding the patient's condition, the health unit assured that "he is in good general condition, isolated, and receiving symptomatic treatment. His close contacts are under strict clinical and epidemiological follow-up, all of them being asymptomatic to date".

The samples for etiological diagnosis were analyzed at the Electron Microscopy Service of the Department of Virology, INEI-ANLIS by Dr Carlos G Malbrán.

