[7] USA
Date: Mon 30 May 2022 11:34 AM PT
Source: TMZ [edited]
https://www.tmz.com/2022/05/30/monkeypox-first-human-transmission-us-epidemic/


The newly-discovered cases of monkeypox in the US are growing at a concerning rate and health officials might have found the 1st cases that involve person-to-person contact within our borders.

In the USA, 4 more monkeypox cases have been detected, with one in Colorado being looked at as a "close contact" of another infected person they examined the day before.

Another close contact was found in California, with someone who had been around an infected patient 3 days prior.

Infection cases have risen to 14 people across 8 states and countries around the globe have seen spikes in cases, with the World Health Organization upgrading the crisis threat level to "moderate."

[A map summarizes the timeline of these cases https://imagez.tmz.com/image/9c/4by3/2022/05/30/9ce02d3d273f4b3da4e9a9a843bc0561_md.jpg]
18 May: Boston, MA (after coming back from Canada)
19 May: New York City, NY (Bellevue Hospital?)
22 May: Fort Lauderdale, FL (Broward County) (related to international travel)
23 May: Salt Lake City, UT (2 cases, traveled to an area in Europe earlier this month [May 2022])
24 May: King County, WA (recently traveled to a country where other monkeypox cases had been identified)
24 May: Sacramento, CA (close contact)
26 May: Virginia (Northern region)(recent international travel history to an African country where the disease is known to occur)
26 May: Colorado (Denver-area man who had recently traveled from Canada)
26 May: Colorado (close contact)

