[A 27 May 2022 report indicated that the Colorado Department of Public Health and Environment Public Health has confirmed a 2nd presumptive monkeypox case and is awaiting CDC confirmation. The 2nd case is a person who was a close contact of the person who is the 1st presumptive monkeypox case in Colorado (https://denver.cbslocal.com/2022/05/27/colorado-second-presumptive-monkeypox-case/).

Several of these cases acquired their infections while traveling internationally. Individuals who plan to travel abroad should be aware of a 27 May 2022 travel alert level 2 (Practice enhanced precautions) travel advisory issued by the USA CDC. As the COVID-19 situation around the world changes, CDC is monitoring COVID-19 risk in each country and making travel recommendations. If one is considering international travel, see CDC's COVID-19 Travel Recommendations by Destination. (https://wwwnc.cdc.gov/travel/notices/alert/monkeypox). - Mod.TY]

